      "width": 760,
      "height": 200,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## What to look for\n\n1) **Multi-label edges**\n- Start label near the source\n- Middle label on the center segment\n- End label near the target\n\n2) **Multi-edge spacing**\n- Two edges from Source → Clean are parallel and should not overlap.\n\n3) **Backwards compatibility**\n- One edge uses legacy `edge.label` and should still render a middle label.",
        "_classBinding": {
